    <section id="food-menu">
      <h2 class="food-menu-heading">Food Menu</h2>
      <div class="food-menu-container container">
        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Dizi-Abgoosht-iranian-cuisine-essential-iran-dishes-cheetah-adventures.jpg" alt="" />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Abgusht</h2>
            <p>
              Abgoosht is prepared by boiling meat, beans, and potatoes for a long time.
               It’s served with Sangak (a type of Iranian bread), onions, herbs, Torshi, and Doogh. 
              
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: $ 25</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img
              src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Persian-Chicken-Kabab-Joojeh-Kabab-Iranian-dishes-Iran-Culture-rotated-e1589120898157.jpg"
              alt="error"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Jujeh Kabab (chicken kebab)</h2>
            <p>
              It is made of chicken breasts, wings and thighs flavored with saffron, spices, and lemon juice and then grilled on a coal fire.
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: <span class="dollar"> $25</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/AshIranian-soup-Iranian-dishes-Iran-Culture-3.jpg" alt="" />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Ash reshteh</h2>
            <p>
              Ash is the name given to traditional Iranian soups; however, it’s very different from the soup. It is denser than normal soup and usually contains herbs and beans.
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: $ 25</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Ghormeh-Sabzi-Iranian-dishes-Iran-Culture.jpg" alt="" />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Khoresht Qorme sabzi</h2>
            <p>
              This appetizing stew contains aromatic herbs, kidney beans, onions, dried lemon and chopped mutton, veal, or lamb.
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: $ 25</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Fesenjan-Iranian-dishes-Iran-Culture.jpg" alt="" />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Khoresht Fesenjoon</h2>
            <p>
              You can choose it to be Sour or sweet contains walnuts, pomegranate paste, and chicken or meatballs.
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: $ 25</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-menu-item">
          <div class="food-img">
            <img src="https://cheetah-adventures.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Tahchin-Iranian-dishes-Iran-Culture.jpg" alt="" />
          </div>
          <div class="food-description">
            <h2 class="food-titile">Tahchin</h2>
            <p>
             rice mixed with yogurt and saffron that has layers of chicken or meat inside.
            </p>
            <p class="food-price">Price: $ 25</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
